    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - CYLINDER HEAD REMOVAL - CRANKCASE
        BREATHER
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CRANKCASE BREATHER</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removal</title>
            <para>Remove crankcase breather as follows (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150408">4.8</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ):
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove bolt and washers from lower breather tube (1).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove mounting bolt and washers from breather tube support (8).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove clamp (2) from breather housing assembly (5).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the bolts and washers which retain the breather housing (5).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the breather tubes and housing assembly removed, remove and discard the gasket (7)
                    and breather element (6).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Reassembly</title>
            <para>Reassemble crankcase breather as follows (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150408">4.8</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ):
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new breather element into the breather baffle.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The breather element has two sides (one side with mesh and one side without mesh). Install
                            with the net facing inside (towards the valve cover).
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a new gasket, install the breather housing to the valve cover. Tighten bolts and
                    washers to the
                    <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150402.xml" xrefid="hl4150402">"SPECIAL TORQUES"</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble the breather hose to the housing assembly with clamp.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure the tubes to the cylinder head and crankcase by installing the bolts and washers
                    at the two clamp locations.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4150408" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg10372" filename="../figcg1/cg10372.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.8. Crankcase Breather</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">1. Lower Breather Tube</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">2. Clamps</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">3. Upper Breather Tube</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">4. Hose</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">5. Breather Housing Assembly</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">6. Breather Element</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">7. Breather Gasket</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">8. Breather Tube Support</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
